26/10/2003
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Danish Prime Minister Anders Fogh Rasmussen met with senior government officials in Skopje on Friday (24 October) to discuss EU integration. Rasmussen was unequivocal in his message:Macedonia's road to EU entry requires implementation of the Ohrid Agreement. He also urged authorities to adopt the draft law on power decentralisation by year's end. (MIA, BBC - 24/10/03)
